Subject: Re: [T2] Carb Synch, am I doing it right?

At 06:31 AM 09/22/2001 +0000, you wrote:

>The old Clymer manual that I have says to check 
>sychronization at 2500-3500 rpm's. Bentley, the "idiot" 
>book, and the delorto tech book all imply that it be 
>checked at idle. 
>Any advice will be greatly appreciated
>thanks
>Mike 72 Westy

With linkage disconnected, you must syncronize the baffels at idle AND with
linkage connected, you must also sychronize the linkage off idle. You must
syncronize both for balanced idle and running.
T.P. Stephens
